HEADWORD: Cragged
<hw>Crag"ged</hw> <pr>(-g⟦ecr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Full of crags,
or steep, broken rocks; abounding with prominences, points, and
inequalities; rough; rugged.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Into its <qex>cragged</qex> rents descend.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Baillie.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Craggedness</ent>⟦br⟧
